        <h1>
            Using Git and GitHub
        </h1>

        <p>
            Some guidelines for using Git and GitHub in the DevOps class (and
            perhaps in other, future classes as well).
        </p>

        <ul class="nested">
            <li>
                Use <i>real</i> commit messages that give someone viewing the
                commit an idea of what occurred.
                <br />
                <b>Bad</b>: "Updated a file."
                <br />
                <b>Good</b>: "Started work on git page and
                added section on commit messages."
            </li>

        </ul>


